QUALIFIER.NAME: Description
QUALIFIER.VALUE: A representation of the SettingData of an SSH endpoint.

QUALIFIER.NAME: Description
QUALIFIER.VALUE: An array of integers indicating the version or versions of SSH protocol that will be enabled for the SSH endpoint.

QUALIFIER.NAME: Description
QUALIFIER.VALUE: When the EnabledSSHVersions property contains a value of 1, "Other" then this is a free form string providing more information about the SSH protocol. If not set to 1, this string has no meaning.

QUALIFIER.NAME: Description
QUALIFIER.VALUE: The version of SSH that will be in use if this SettingData is applied.

QUALIFIER.NAME: Description
QUALIFIER.VALUE: If the CurrentSSHVersion property is set to 1, "Other" then this is a free form string providing more information about the current SSH protocol. If not set to 1, this string has no meaning.

QUALIFIER.NAME: Description
QUALIFIER.VALUE: An array of integers indicating the encryption algorithms that are enabled for this SSH service. Its possible for an encryption algorithm to be supported and not currently enabled to be used.

QUALIFIER.NAME: Description
QUALIFIER.VALUE: If the EnabledEncryptionAlgorithms property is set 1, "Other" this property contains a free form string providing more information about supported algorithms. If not set to 1, this string has no meaning.

QUALIFIER.NAME: Description
QUALIFIER.VALUE: The encryption algorithm that will be in use if this SettingData is applied.

QUALIFIER.NAME: Description
QUALIFIER.VALUE: If the EncryptionAlgorithm property is set 1, "Other" then this is a free form string providing more information about the encryption algorithm in use. If not set to 1, this string has no meaning.

QUALIFIER.NAME: Description
QUALIFIER.VALUE: IdleTimeout specifies how long the connection can be idle before the connection is terminated. The default value, 0, indicates that there is no idle timeout period.

QUALIFIER.NAME: Description
QUALIFIER.VALUE: If this property is true, the SSH keep alive timer is enabled.

QUALIFIER.NAME: Description
QUALIFIER.VALUE: If this property is true, the SSH X11 forwarding mode is enabled.

QUALIFIER.NAME: Description
QUALIFIER.VALUE: If this property is true, SSH compression is enabled.

QUALIFIER.NAME: Description
QUALIFIER.VALUE: Within the scope of the instantiating Namespace, InstanceID opaquely and uniquely identifies an instance of this class. To ensure uniqueness within the NameSpace, the value of InstanceID should be constructed using the following "preferred" algorithm: <OrgID>:<LocalID> Where <OrgID> and <LocalID> are separated by a colon (:), and where <OrgID> must include a copyrighted, trademarked, or otherwise unique name that is owned by the business entity that is creating or defining the InstanceID or that is a registered ID assigned to the business entity by a recognized global authority. (This requirement is similar to the <Schema Name>_<Class Name> structure of Schema class names.) In addition, to ensure uniqueness, <OrgID> must not contain a colon (:). When using this algorithm, the first colon to appear in InstanceID must appear between <OrgID> and <LocalID>. <LocalID> is chosen by the business entity and should not be reused to identify different underlying (real-world) elements. If the above "preferred" algorithm is not used, the defining entity must assure that the resulting InstanceID is not reused across any InstanceIDs produced by this or other providers for the NameSpace of this instance. For DMTF-defined instances, the "preferred" algorithm must be used with the <OrgID> set to CIM.

QUALIFIER.NAME: Description
QUALIFIER.VALUE: The user-friendly name for this instance of SettingData. In addition, the user-friendly name can be used as an index property for a search or query. (Note: The name does not have to be unique within a namespace.)

QUALIFIER.NAME: Description
QUALIFIER.VALUE: Enumeration indicating the type of setting. 0 "Not Changeable - Persistent" indicates the instance of SettingData represents primordial settings and shall not be modifiable. 1 "Changeable - Transient" indicates the SettingData represents modifiable settings that are not persisted. Establishing persistent settings from transient settings may be supported. 2 "Changeable - Persistent" indicates the SettingData represents a persistent configuration that may be modified. 3 "Not Changeable - Transient" indicates the SettingData represents a snapshot of the settings of the associated ManagedElement and is not persistent.

QUALIFIER.NAME: Description
QUALIFIER.VALUE: An instance of CIM_SettingData may correspond to a well-known configuration that exists for an associated CIM_ManagedElement. If the ConfigurationName property is non-NULL, the instance of CIM_SettingData shall correspond to a well-known configuration for a Managed Element, the value of the ConfigurationName property shall be the name of the configuration, and the ChangeableType property shall have the value 0 or 2. A value of NULL for the ConfigurationName property shall mean that the instance of CIM_SettingData does not correspond to a well-known configuration for a Managed Element or that this information is unknown.

QUALIFIER.NAME: Description
QUALIFIER.VALUE: The Caption property is a short textual description (one- line string) of the object.

QUALIFIER.NAME: Description
QUALIFIER.VALUE: The Description property provides a textual description of the object.
